    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@benjaminion seems like, for your case, you were missing the `--metrics-interface=0.0.0.0`, which would have made Teku metrics visible to remote hosts. The only reason Rest API worked without `--rest-api-interface=0.0.0.0`, is because of this issue we apparently have: https://github.com/PegaSysEng/teku/issues/2213. So if you provide those flags, your metrics should be accessible from remote hosts. Closing this issue as I'm pretty sure that will fix your problem, but let me know and we can open it up again.",
